<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1535" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1535">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.48.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Expenditure of $1,000 for food supplies authorized by American Reel
                            Cross, in pursuance of your August 5. Supplies will be furnished for
                            delivery to <hi rend="italic">Justin</hi> to be held at Corinto subject
                            to your instructions. These supplies will be furnished by commissary
                            department of Canal Commission under the direction of the American
                            Minister at Panama.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>